On Saturday February 15th, join @livecodenyc for Love Death Code: our HALLOWEEN ON VALENTINES tradition. Feel equal parts ❤️ love ❤️ and 💀 terror 💀 at the intersection of 😱 art 😱 and 💻 technology 💻! Come for the performances, stay for the 👻 COSTUME CONTEST 👻~ Our categories are loveliest, deathliest, and most computer.
Livecode.NYC
is a New York City-based artist collective devoted to the real-time programming technique called livecoding, and exploring its potential as a methodology of artistic expressions. This leaderless collective has no formal membership or hierarchy; anyone is welcome to join, attend, and host events. Our members include artists, engineers, actors, designers, educators, musicians, game developers, and writers. We view live coding as a process-driven practice and not specific to a particular medium or language. This event will have individuals live coding music and visuals through programs like tidal cycles, hydra, unreal engine, and custom made technologies.
